### Events

v-on listens for an event

Any time there is a v-on directive, event object is automaticly passed to the method that is listening for the event
Event object can be accessed in the HMLT with '$event'
$event is protected variable. Also, you only need to use 'event' to access in the JS code.

you can stop v-on with '.stop' added to the ened of the v-on:MODIFIER

